<text id="05-examples" title="Meta Ads Reporting and Diagnosis Worked Example" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="800" depth="medium">
  <summary>One end-to-end worked example showing the methodology applied to a realistic scenario, including the produced artefact.</summary>
  <example type="good">
    <description>Faion SaaS Meta wk21: $5.2k spend, CPA $32 (target $30), frequency 2.7. Diagnosis: creative_fatigue on top-2 ad set; reels placement carries lift.</description>
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "period": {
    "start": "2026-05-16",
    "end": "2026-05-22"
  },
  "metrics": {
    "spend": 5200,
    "cpm": 18.4,
    "ctr": 0.014,
    "cpc": 1.32,
    "cvr": 0.041,
    "cpa": 32.1,
    "roas": 3.6,
    "frequency": 2.7
  },
  "breakdowns": [
    {
      "dimension": "placement",
      "rows": [
        {
          "placement": "reels",
          "cpa": 22.0
        },
        {
          "placement": "feed",
          "cpa": 41.0
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "diagnoses": [
    {
      "symptom": "frequency_2.7",
      "root_cause": "creative_fatigue",
      "evidence": "CTR -28% wk/wk; freq 1.9\u21922.7"
    }
  ],
  "actions": [
    {
      "priority": 1,
      "lever": "rotate_creative_bottom2",
      "expected_impact": "CPA -15%",
      "owner": "creative"
    },
    {
      "priority": 2,
      "lever": "shift_budget_to_reels",
      "expected_impact": "CPA -8%",
      "owner": "ops"
    }
  ]
}
    ]]></code>
    <note>Symptom→root-cause map applied; actions quantified + owned.</note>
  </example>
</text>
